(firstQuint)Taste and Palatability of Orfadin Suspension.

 This is an open, non-randomized, non-controlled, multiple-dose study in 18 pediatric patients.

 The treatment period is three days, and during the study the subjects will rate the taste and palatability of the suspension or (for younger children) their parents will rate the childs acceptance of the suspension.

 The study consists of a screening period, a 3 day treatment period and a 1 week follow-up period.

